# Project Overview

This is Andrew Ambrosino's personal portfolio website built with modern web technologies.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 15 with App Router
- **Language**: TypeScript with strict mode
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 with CSS variables
- **UI Components**: shadcn/ui (New York style) with Radix UI primitives
- **Icons**: Tabler Icons and Lucide React
- **Fonts**: Geist Sans and Geist Mono
- **Theme**: Dark/light mode support with next-themes
- **Package Manager**: pnpm

## Architecture
The site uses Next.js App Router with a sidebar-based layout:
- Root layout in [app/layout.tsx](mdc:app/layout.tsx) provides global theme and sidebar
- Pages are organized under [app/(pages)/](mdc:app/(pages)/) route group
- Components are split between [components/](mdc:components/) and [components/ui/](mdc:components/ui/)
- Utilities and hooks are in [lib/](mdc:lib/) and [hooks/](mdc:hooks/) respectively

## Key Features
- Responsive sidebar navigation with collapsible sections
- Dark/light theme switching
- MDX support for content pages
- Professional timeline component for work experience
- Modern typography with custom font loading
